title: The Baroque Era (Life, Times and Music - Art Ebook)
description:
pdf / English / 76 pages / 1992 / 8.4 MB

The Baroque era was the bridge between the Renaissance and the Enlightenment, a time when oppressive politics were cast aside and the rights of the individual were celebrated. It was an era that embraced, among others, Newton, Rembrandt, Rubens, Vivaldi, and J. S. Bach. Listen to and enjoy the great music while you learn about the events and ideas that made this music possible
